## ğŸš€ Installation & Setup

Below are universal instructions that work on **Windows**, **macOS**, and **Linux**.

### 1. Clone the repository

```bash
git clone https://github.com/BrindirCoder/flask-task-manager.git
cd taskflow-flask

2. Create a virtual environment

Windows

python -m venv venv
venv\Scripts\activate


macOS / Linux

python3 -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate

3. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

4. Initialize the database
flask db init
flask db migrate -m "Initial migration"
flask db upgrade

5. Run the application
flask run


App will be available at:
http://127.0.0.1:5000

ğŸ›  Configuration

You can configure the database or environment by editing:

instance/config.py


Or by passing environment variables such as:

export FLASK_APP=app.py
export FLASK_ENV=development
